07.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.talonswitch.com/qamgine.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Missing Rotational Targets</span><hr size=1> I thought I would post this here as well. I posted this, this morning on KGC. I think it would behove everyone to at least read through it.<br>
<br>
----------- My Post on KGC--<br>
KGC is turning into the biggest joke due to everyone's lack of apathy and gumption to get off their duffs and take care of something. Everything KGC has strived to stand for, is being walked on by a few select people. Guilded or not, it makes little to no difference. People are getting lazy with taking down mobs. These few people are tired of seeing good loot and mobs basically &quot;rot&quot; by not being killed.<br>
With level 65 and AA points of the plenty, it will only take a party of 2 groups to take down what most of us would need 5 groups to take down. Most of our Rotation mobs are being compared to PoP's yard-trash.<br>
<br>
This server is LARGE, it has already been split once, and IMHO needs another one. The server has created a bureaucratic organization that works to help ALL people, no matter size of guild, race, or class! The people that are doing this only care about them, and not everyone else.<br>
<br>
Yeah, they have friends, their own click sticks, etc. With the release of PoP, ports are rarely needed. They probably have gear that most would just only dream of having. They probably play close to 24/7 and have some other form of income (parents) or what not. SOE designed this game to be for both the advid, and casual gamer. However, these people don't care about that. In their eyes, if you are casual, you are not worthy of playing this game. &quot;Survival of the fittest&quot; was quoted on one board.<br>
<br>
You know what? I'm an exceptionally casual player. Most here, have probably never heard of Royal Knights of Light. Frankly, there is nothing that I can do to stop this. By myself that is. We as Karana can. How? By hitting these mobs pronto and taking them down. Leaving them up for 48, 72, etc hours is annoying.<br>
<br>
Most mob rotations allow for at least 1 if not many more months in between. In that time, you should be running mini-raids to &quot;improve&quot; your raiding skills. Yeah, I'll admit at times, the dice just don't roll in your favor. Things happen. But, when you come up for a mob, you should have had a bit of &quot;training&quot; prior to at least know what you are supposed to do.<br>
<br>
Can we threaten these KSers? No. Can we Blacklist them? Sure, but from the looks of it, they have more resources than most here. We really only have one &quot;valid&quot; non-bannable choice. Engage and take our targets down before they can. If KGC is diligent in taking down it's targets then these rogue players are left with either getting a life and going to PoP mobs, or going on the rotation.<br>
<br>
/rant<br>
I pay my monthy fee just like everyone else here. This is not Unreal tournament where the player with the most frags wins. There is no real &quot;Ending&quot; to this game. Yet these rogue players are turning it into that. If you want a challenge of pure RPG - go to a red server and get yourself Pk-ed a couple of times. Try and KS a target and see how many darks enter a zone ready to wipe the place with your carcass. In some ways, I enjoyed being on PVP, in others I hated it. But one thing was for sure, people didn't sit around on their duffs when something like this happens. So far, all that's been done is a bunch of complaining in MB's.<br>
<br>
Yeah, I'm complaining, but I'm a low man on the totem!! I couldn't stop someone from taking a most mobs, much less a rot target. Karana guilds are sitting on their duffs with their finger up their nose hoping this will just go away. No offense to anyone, but because no one here wants to do anything about it, the lower guilds are getting hurt more.<br>
<br>
Yeah the rotations are LONG. Not everything is perfect. But, KGC has &quot;worked&quot; because we all feel as though this is for the benefit of the &quot;entire SERVER&quot;. Now we are just sitting back and watching this happen, and we are being joked about.<br>
<br>
If YOU don't do anything, it isn't going to get done. Man, if I coming from a smaller guild know that, you should! This can be stopped, but only if we work together and get take our finger out of our nose and get some gumption!!<br>
<br>
Don't mind mobs being Perma-Kill? Don't mind FFA? Don't care about your Epic? Fine, but do me a favor, get off of Karana. It's too big for people like that. Go to a smaller server where there aren't as many guilds stealing all the mobs.<br>
<br>
And to the Rogue Guilds (yeah, I'm sure you are reading this), if you want a challenge, go PVP. Just try this over there. It may last one or two times, but guaranteed you will see the server join together to take you down and make sure you feel the blisters afterward.<br>
<br>
My hope is that Karana can get some of that inspiration that this is OUR server and we aren't going to let some jerks perma-kill the mobs.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
<br>
What are you going to do about this?<br>
<br>
------------------<br>
Qamgine Nighteagle<br>
Fearless Leader~<br>
Royal Knights of Light<br>
&quot;If you even think of cooking me, there'll be trouble!&quot;<br>
Ranger of Karana<br>
KCoG Companion<br>
